or love and kindness.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nYou were nothing more than a daydream that a beautiful heart was bound to fall in love with, and daydreams aren't real and beautiful hearts trust easily, fall fast and crash hard.\n\n- Melody  Lee, Moon Gypsy\n|\nRise to become human again, my friend. Become the human, that talks humans, acts humans and lives human.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, Wise Mating: A Treatise on Monogamy\n|\nThe power of a boy's dream is one of life's little miracles, the way it wraps itself around the heart and remains through old age to the last breath.\n\n- Tom Verducci, The Cubs Way: The Zen of Building the Best Team in Baseball and Breaking the Curse\n|\nDon't appreciate me, I'm not up to it. Don't criticize me, I don't deserve it. Just be my friend and forgive me, because I am craving for it.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nSmart people have the brains, but stupid people have the balls\n\n- Ana\n|\nI had decided to stop chasing the money, and start chasing the passion.\n\n- Tony Hsieh, Delivering Happiness: A Path to Profits, Passion, and Purpose\n|\nFear, anxiety, stress and panic, all these are basic evolutionary expression of the human brain. They are part of the normal human condition.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, The Islamophobic Civilization: Voyage of Acceptance\n|\nThe Gospel of peace, must be preach to all people.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nDo not doubt thyself, have faith in thy soul.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nWhile you try to make peace on earth, the inhabitants of heaven are still at war.\n\n- Toba Beta, Master of Stupidity\n|\nTruly, art is embedded in nature; he who can extract it, has it.\n\n- Albrecht\n|\nThat faceless, nameless and ruthless demon you pretend to fight, is nothing but the bastard in your head.\n\n- Mamur\n|\nTo be the master of tomorrow's dreams, you must first be the servant of today's planning.\n\n- Vincent\n|\nThe first step away from being manipulated, and towards a more autonomous outlook, is to stand back from a set of responses and think.\n\n- Jonathan Glover, Causing Death and Saving Lives\n|\nMarcii hoped she was wrong, though she knew the odds were slim.Still, in the face of everything, there is always hope.\n\n- Ross  Turner, Reaper\n|\nIt’s an already inside outside,The philosophers say it’s the soulBut it’s not the soul: it’s the animal or the man itselfIn its way of existing.\n\n- Alberto Caeiro, The Collected Poems of Alberto Caeiro"